Functionality: common logic for serialization, will hold the includes, allow easily override serialization for the whole project (eg turn it off for some fork of nupic,...)

API:

```
import capnp...

__init__(type='capnp')
def serialize():
  if self.type == 'off':
    return
  return write()
def deserialize(obj):
  if self.type == 'off':
    return
  return read()
getType() # 'oldpy', 'capnp', 'off'
def write():
  raise # implment in your code
def read():
  raise # to implement
```

Classes: all that support, or should, serialization. Example: `MyClass: super(MyClass, self).__init__(type='off')`

[`nupic/ntypes/NodeSet.hpp` uses the macro `NTA_THROW`](https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/blob/master/src/nupic/ntypes/NodeSet.hpp#L86), which is defined in [`nupic/utils/Log.hpp`](https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/blob/master/src/nupic/utils/Log.hpp#L49), but it does not include that file. Therefore builds will only succeed when a file imports `Log.hpp` before importing `NodeSet.hpp`.

This should be fixed by including `Log.hpp` in `NodeSet.hpp`.

