```python
class ParallelDataset(Dataset):

    @abstractmethod
    def build(self):
        pass
```

The `build` command would be executed in the beginning of the (parallel) worker function, specifically in this line: https://github.com/kipoi/kipoi/blob/master/kipoi/external/torch/data.py#L46. This would allow us to setup the file handles for each process separately. Namely, since this PR: https://github.com/kundajelab/genomelake/pull/5, the fasta file handle is shared between different processes resulting in occasional failures.
